# Technical Master Blueprint: Automation-Infinite (Sovereign AGI)

This document is the **Surgical Technical Specification** for building the Sovereign AGI layer. Correcting previous strategic gaps, this blueprint defines the exact mechanics of agency, state, and safety.

---

## 🏗️ 1. The Global State Object (Data Flow)

To ensure seamless coordination between agents (The Forge, the Sentinel, the Oracle), all modules operate on a shared **Sovereign State (S-State)**.

### 11.1 S-State Schema (JSON)
```json
{
  "protocol_version": "1.0",
  "active_persona": { "id": "CRITICAL_COMPOSITE", "weights": { "risk": 0.8, "synergy": 0.5 } },
  "system_telemetry": { "cpu_load": 0.45, "vram_usage": "8/12GB", "network_status": "Secure-Mesh" },
  "memory_tape": [ { "agent": "Forge", "action": "Init-Repo", "status": "Success", "timestamp": "..." } ],
  "spend_valve": { "tier": 3, "monthly_budget": 50.00, "used": 12.45, "pending_approvals": [] },
  "active_objectives": [ { "id": "OBJ001", "description": "Shadow Build Hangout-Hub v2", "priority": "High" } ]
}
```
**Mechanism**: Agents do not send messages; they **mutate the state**. When the `S-State` is updated, the parent orchestrator (The General) triggers relevant sub-agents via a Pub/Sub model.

